# Novaël — Project Conventions

Luxury women's beauty e-commerce SPA. Brand voice: minimalist, expensive, quiet confidence (Chanel-adjacent).

## Stack

- **React 19 + Vite 8** (SPA, no SSR). JS only — no TypeScript. All files are `.jsx` / `.js`.
- **Tailwind CSS 3** (extends `tailwind.config.js` from CSS variables in `src/styles/tokens.css`)
- **Supabase** (`@supabase/supabase-js`) for auth + DB. Frontend-only; no Node backend.
- **Zustand** for global state (`src/store/`). `persist` middleware for cart only.
- **React Router 7** (`BrowserRouter`, lazy routes, `AnimatePresence` page fades).
- **Framer Motion 12** for all animations.
- **Radix UI** for Dialog (Modal), Toast, Accordion, Dropdown, Tabs, Tooltip, Select.
- **Recharts** — admin charts only.
- **react-hook-form + zod + @hookform/resolvers** for forms.
- **react-helmet-async** for per-page SEO meta.
- **lucide-react** for icons. (Note: `Instagram` icon was removed — see `Footer.jsx` for custom SVG fallbacks for Instagram/TikTok/Pinterest.)

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── auth/          AuthShell (split-screen wrapper)
│   ├── cart/          CartDrawer, CartItem
│   ├── common/        Logo, GoldDivider, AnimatedReveal, SearchOverlay
│   ├── layout/        Navbar, Footer, MainLayout, AdminLayout
│   ├── product/       ProductCard, ProductGrid
│   └── ui/            Button, Input, Badge, Modal, Toast, Spinner  ← primitives
├── config/brand.js    Brand copy, nav config, values, marquee, categories
├── hooks/             useProducts, useOrders, usePromo, useWishlist, useAdmin
├── lib/               supabase.js (client), utils.js (cn, formatters, totals)
├── pages/             One file per route. Admin pages under pages/admin/
├── routes/            AppRouter, ProtectedRoute
├── store/             cartStore (persisted), authStore
└── styles/            tokens.css, globals.css
```

## Naming Conventions

- Components: `PascalCase.jsx` (default export named the same).
- Hooks: `useThing.js`, return an object `{ data, loading, error, ... }`.
- Stores: `xxxStore.js`, exported as `useXxxStore`.
- Utility functions: `camelCase` in `src/lib/utils.js`.
- Tailwind classes are merged via `cn(...)` from `src/lib/utils.js` (clsx + tailwind-merge). **Always use `cn` when conditionally combining classes.**

## Design Tokens (single source of truth)

Defined in `src/styles/tokens.css` and mirrored in `tailwind.config.js`. **Never hardcode hex colors in components — use Tailwind utilities (`bg-gold`, `text-ivory`, etc.).**

| Color | Hex | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `black` | `#0E0E0E` | primary background, dark surfaces |
| `ivory` | `#F6F3EE` | text on dark, light surfaces |
| `gold` | `#C6A97A` | the only accent. Borders, hovers, CTAs, dividers |
| `plum` | `#2D133A` | rare accent (badges) |
| `mauve` | `#B79BBF` | rare accent (status badges) |
| `rose-nude` | `#E8C6C6` | error / destructive state |
| `taupe` | `#A8A17A` | muted text, line-through prices |
| `admin-bg` `#0A0A0A`, `admin-surface` `#141414` | admin only |

Typography:
- **`font-display`** = Cinzel (headlines, logo, labels). Always `uppercase` + wide tracking (`tracking-[0.15em]` to `tracking-[0.3em]`).
- **`font-body`** = Montserrat (paragraphs, inputs). Default body has `letter-spacing: 0.03em`.
- Headlines `<h1>`–`<h6>` are pre-styled in `globals.css` (display font, `letter-spacing: 0.12em`).

## Absolute Rules

- ❌ **No hardcoded hex colors.** Use Tailwind tokens (`text-gold`, `bg-ivory`, etc.).
- ❌ **No new fonts.** Cinzel + Montserrat only.
- ❌ **No npm packages added without need.** The stack above is intentionally tight.
- ❌ **No CSS files per component.** Tailwind utilities + `globals.css` brand classes only.
- ❌ **No emojis in UI.** Use `lucide-react` icons (or custom SVG components like `InstagramIcon` in `Footer.jsx`).
- ❌ **No `console.log`** in committed code (`console.warn` for genuine warnings is fine — see `lib/supabase.js`).
- ❌ **No `<a href>` for internal links** — use `<Link>` from react-router-dom.
- ✅ Use the brand utility classes from `globals.css` when applicable: `.btn-luxe` (+ `--filled`/`--dark`), `.link-luxe`, `.gold-divider`, `.skeleton`, `.grain-overlay`, `.container-nvl`.
- ✅ All money is rendered via `formatPrice(value)` from `lib/utils.js`.
- ✅ All dates via `formatDate` / `formatDateTime` from `lib/utils.js`.
- ✅ Page-level meta via `<Helmet>` (provider already in `main.jsx`).

## Common Imports Cheatsheet

```js
import { cn, formatPrice, formatDate } from '@/lib/utils'   // (alias not configured — use relative)
import { supabase } from '../lib/supabase'
import { useCartStore } from '../store/cartStore'
import { useAuthStore } from '../store/authStore'
import { toast } from '../components/ui/Toast.jsx'
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.jsx'
import { Input, Textarea } from '../components/ui/Input.jsx'
```

Path imports use **relative paths**, not aliases. Don't introduce a path alias without updating `vite.config.js` first.
